Temecula.Pauba Valley:
Pauba Valley, is a valley along the course of Temecula Creek, in Riverside County, California.
It heads to the east at 33°30′06″N 117°00′10″W, the mouth of the gorge of Temecula Creek Canyon at the foot of Oak Mountain. Its mouth in the west is at an elevation of 1014 feet / 309 meters, where it joins the Elsinore Trough at the confluence of Wolf Valley and Temecula Valley.
